        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:26AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1126 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Troy, or 9 miles southwest of Union City, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mason Hall, Mount Pelia, Old Fremont, Gibbs, Moffatt, Union City,
Troy, Obion, Shaffner, Wolverine, Terrell, Rives, McCutchen Heights,
Fremont, and Woodland Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
